The paper focuses on introducing computer science to high school students through logic programming, which falls under the programming languages (PL) subcategory. Additionally, the paper discusses how novice students approach computing in the LP paradigm, which is relevant to education (ED) and logic (LO) subcategories. The paper also touches on the use of LP in artificial intelligence (AI) and the revision/debugging process, which relates to software engineering (SE).
